question_text: How do you open Chrome DevTools?
explanation: Pressing F12 opens DevTools quickly on most browsers.

question_text: Which panel inspects HTML and CSS?
explanation: Elements panel shows DOM structure and styles.

question_text: What does the Console panel display?
explanation: Console shows JavaScript logs, errors, and warnings.

question_text: How to inspect a specific element?
explanation: Right-click and select Inspect to view element in Elements panel.

question_text: Which panel shows network requests?
explanation: Network panel monitors all HTTP requests and responses.

question_text: How to clear console output?
explanation: Use console.clear() or type clear() in console to clear messages.

question_text: What does the Sources panel do?
explanation: Sources panel allows JavaScript debugging and file viewing.

question_text: How to set a breakpoint?
explanation: Click on line number in Sources panel to set breakpoint.

question_text: What does the Application panel store?
explanation: Application panel manages local storage, cookies, and cache.

question_text: How to view cookies in DevTools?
explanation: Go to Application panel and select Cookies under Storage.

question_text: What does console.log() do?
explanation: console.log() prints messages to the Console panel.

question_text: How to inspect mobile view?
explanation: Click device toolbar icon or press Ctrl+Shift+M to toggle.

question_text: What is the Elements panel used for?
explanation: Edit HTML structure and CSS styles in real-time.

question_text: How to edit CSS live?
explanation: Modify CSS in Styles panel and see changes instantly.

question_text: What does the Network panel show?
explanation: Shows all resources loaded by the page.

question_text: How to record a performance profile?
explanation: Click record button in Performance panel to start profiling.

question_text: What does the Lighthouse panel do?
explanation: Lighthouse audits PWA, performance, accessibility, and SEO.

question_text: How to view page source?
explanation: Press Ctrl+U or right-click > View Page Source.

question_text: What is the purpose of color picker?
explanation: Color picker helps select and modify colors in Styles panel.

question_text: How to search in Elements panel?
explanation: Press Ctrl+F to search DOM elements.

question_text: What does console.error() do?
explanation: console.error() prints error messages in red.

question_text: How to disable cache in DevTools?
explanation: Check Disable cache in Network panel or Settings.

question_text: What is the Console drawer?
explanation: Press Esc to open Console drawer with any panel.

question_text: How to view box model in Elements?
explanation: Go to Computed tab in Elements to see box model.

question_text: What does the Security panel show?
explanation: Shows security overview and certificate details.

question_text: How to format minified JavaScript?
explanation: Click {} (Pretty Print) in Sources panel to format code.

question_text: What does the Coverage tab do?
explanation: Coverage shows which code lines execute.

question_text: How to take a screenshot in DevTools?
explanation: Use Command Menu (Ctrl+Shift+P) and type screenshot.

question_text: What does console.warn() do?
explanation: console.warn() prints yellow warning messages.

question_text: How to inspect iframes in DevTools?
explanation: Use dropdown in Elements panel to select iframe context.

question_text: What does the Audits panel do?
explanation: Audits panel (now Lighthouse) runs performance checks.

question_text: How to view event listeners?
explanation: Event Listeners tab in Elements shows attached events.

question_text: What is the Command Menu?
explanation: Press Ctrl+Shift+P to access DevTools commands.

question_text: How to emulate print media?
explanation: Use Rendering tab to emulate print media type.

question_text: What does the Memory panel measure?
explanation: Memory panel measures JavaScript heap memory.

question_text: How to throttle network speed?
explanation: Use throttling dropdown in Network panel to simulate speeds.

question_text: What does the Changes panel show?
explanation: Tracks CSS and JavaScript changes made in DevTools.

question_text: How to copy an element in Elements?
explanation: Right-click element and choose Copy > Copy element.

question_text: What does console.table() do?
explanation: console.table() shows arrays/objects in table format.

question_text: How to view localStorage items?
explanation: Go to Application panel and select Local Storage.

question_text: What is the purpose of the Watch panel?
explanation: Add variables to watch their values during debugging.

question_text: How to simulate geolocation?
explanation: Use Sensors panel in DevTools to override geolocation.

question_text: What does the Quick Source panel show?
explanation: Shows currently edited source file in Sources panel.

question_text: How to find unused CSS?
explanation: Record coverage to see unused CSS and JavaScript.

question_text: What does console.time() measure?
explanation: console.time() measures how long code takes to run.

question_text: How to inspect a hover state?
explanation: Click :hov in Styles and check :hover to simulate.

question_text: What is the purpose of the Issues panel?
explanation: Displays issues like accessibility and security problems.

question_text: How to view all event listeners globally?
explanation: Type getEventListeners(document) in console to see all.

question_text: What does the Animations panel do?
explanation: Record and modify CSS animations in real-time.

question_text: How to search network requests?
explanation: Use filter box in Network panel to search requests.

question_text: What does the Console drawer's Network conditions do?
explanation: Change user agent and network settings in Console drawer.

question_text: How to copy response data in Network?
explanation: Right-click request and select Copy > Copy response.

question_text: What does the Performance monitor show?
explanation: Shows real-time CPU, JS heap, and DOM node counts.

question_text: How to edit HTML directly in Elements?
explanation: Right-click element and choose Edit as HTML.

question_text: What does console.count() do?
explanation: console.count() tracks how many times code executes.

question_text: How to preserve log across pages?
explanation: Check Preserve log in Network panel to keep logs.

question_text: What is the purpose of the Recorder panel?
explanation: Records user interactions for testing and automation.

question_text: How to view CSS grid overlays?
explanation: Use Layout panel in Elements to show grid overlays.

question_text: What does console.group() do?
explanation: Creates collapsible group of console messages.

question_text: How to view service workers?
explanation: Service Workers section in Application panel.

question_text: How to simulate offline mode?
explanation: Set throttling to Offline in Network panel.

question_text: What does the Rendering panel do?
explanation: Controls paint flashing, layout shifts, and media emulation.

question_text: How to delete a cookie in DevTools?
explanation: Select cookie in Application panel and click delete.

question_text: What does console.assert() do?
explanation: console.assert() logs only when assertion fails.

question_text: How to view CSS variables?
explanation: View custom properties in Styles panel under :root.

question_text: What is the purpose of the Search tab in Sources?
explanation: Search all project files for text in Sources panel.

question_text: How to throttle CPU in DevTools?
explanation: Use CPU throttling in Performance panel settings.

question_text: What does the WebAudio panel show?
explanation: Visualizes Web Audio API nodes and connections.

question_text: How to view WebSocket frames?
explanation: Select WebSocket connection and view frames in Messages tab.

question_text: What does console.trace() do?
explanation: console.trace() outputs a stack trace.

question_text: How to use DevTools in a different language?
explanation: Go to Settings and change language preference.

question_text: What does the Shortcuts panel show?
explanation: Shows all DevTools keyboard shortcuts in Settings.

question_text: How to change theme in DevTools?
explanation: Choose light or dark theme in Settings.

question_text: What does the Console's $0 shortcut mean?
explanation: $0 references the last element selected in Elements.

question_text: How to view all JavaScript files loaded?
explanation: Page tab in Sources shows all loaded resources.

question_text: What does the 3-dot menu in DevTools offer?
explanation: Access DevTools settings and more options.

question_text: How to dock DevTools to different sides?
explanation: Use dock icon to change DevTools position.

question_text: What does console.dir() show?
explanation: console.dir() displays interactive object properties.

question_text: How to see CSS changes made?
explanation: Changes panel tracks all CSS modifications.

question_text: What is the purpose of the Media panel?
explanation: Shows media players and their properties.

question_text: How to copy JavaScript object as JSON?
explanation: Use copy() function or right-click object to copy.

question_text: What does the Layers panel show?
explanation: Shows how page is split into GPU layers.

question_text: How to view page performance summary?
explanation: Performance panel provides performance summary.

question_text: What does the Console's $() function do?
explanation: $() is shorthand for document.querySelector().

question_text: How to reset DevTools settings?
explanation: Restore defaults in DevTools Settings.

question_text: What is the difference between console.log and console.info?
explanation: console.info() shows with info icon, console.log() without.

question_text: How to view CSS specificity?
explanation: Styles tab shows selector specificity details.

question_text: What does the Problems panel show?
explanation: Displays code problems and suggested fixes.

question_text: How to simulate prefers-color-scheme?
explanation: Use Rendering panel to emulate dark/light mode.

question_text: What does console.profile() do?
explanation: Starts JavaScript CPU profiling session.

question_text: How to view IndexedDB data?
explanation: IndexedDB section in Application panel shows databases.

question_text: What does the Console's $$() function do?
explanation: $$() selects all elements matching selector.

question_text: How to view font information in Elements?
explanation: Computed tab shows font details for element.

question_text: What does the Memory inspector show?
explanation: View raw memory contents for debugging.

question_text: How to toggle color format in Styles?
explanation: Click color swatch to cycle through formats.
